cs.NI, cs.COMM, cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.AR 

This paper discusses the ATM protocol layers and LAN Emulation and Traffic Management in the context of communication networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). It could also be categorized under cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) and cs.IT (Information Theory) as it discusses the implementation and specification agreements for communication services. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as it discusses the deployment of ATM technology. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) as it discusses the equipment vendors in the communication industries.
